<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd2a8238-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s5326"><num value="5326">§ 5326.</num><heading> “Member of the House” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s5324">section 5324 of this title</ref> the phrase “Member of the House” shall mean a Representative, Representative-elect, Delegate, Delegate-elect, Resident Commissioner, or Resident Commissioner-elect.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddd2a8239-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(<ref href="/us/act/1935-08-21/ch600/s3">Aug. 21, 1935, ch. 600, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/49/680">49 Stat. 680</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddd2a823a-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddd2a823b-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddd2a823c-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s92d">section 92d of this title</ref> prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="iddd2a823d-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="iddd2a823e-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1935-01-03">Jan. 3, 1935</date>, see section 4 of act <date date="1935-08-21">Aug. 21, 1935</date>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s5324">section 5324 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
